






#lg A	sa-gida


@(1-8=c25409.A.1) August chariot! @wDN{Enlil}, the lord of wisdom, the father of the gods, ordered your construction in the @wTN{E-kur}, his exalted shrine. He instructed @wRN{Išme-@wDN{Dagan}}, the wise shepherd called by an auspicious name, born from a beautiful mother's womb, the adviser of the Land, to make your holy and pure divine powers manifest. He set to work on you and worked without stopping. He decorated you with …… and lapis lazuli. He placed you …….

@(9-18=c25409.A.9) Your two …… are something to be marvelled at. Your furnishings are most outstanding, like a forest of aromatic cedars. Your pole is a field with open furrows, an abundance of dappled grain. Your …… is a thick cloud covering the …… of heaven all over. Your yoke is a huge neck-stock from which there is no escape, which clamps down the evildoer. Your rope-fastened pegs are laid down as a huge net spanning heaven and earth.

$ (1 line fragmentary)
$ (1 line missing)
$ (1 line fragmentary)

@(19-21=c25409.A.19) Your side-poles (?) are …… subduing the hostile countries. Your …… of the side-poles are …….

$ (6 lines missing)

@(28-40=c25409.A.28) Your mudguard is @wDN{Utu} …… the horizon, ……. The front of your mudguard is the ornament of (?) ……. Your implements are @wDN{Nanna} who fills the midst of heaven with delight. Your axle is …… which …… a flood. Your rope-box is a whip …… which rouses up the donkeys. Your pole-pin is a huge open battle-net which does not let the evildoer escape. Your farings are the exalted princely divine powers sought out with great care. Your platform is warriors fiercely attacking each other. Your side beams are strong breeding bulls carrying a heavy load. Your cross-beams are urgent young men embracing each other. Your side-boards are ……. Your foot-board is ……. Your seat …….
$ (21 lines missing)

@(62-64=c25409.A.62) At that time @wRN{Išme-@wDN{Dagan}} …… decorated the chariot with silver, gold, and lapis lazuli for his king, @wDN{Enlil}.

